    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM ANCHORLOK SPRING BRAKE - BRAKE CHAMBER SERVICE - RE-INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>RE-INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pin the spring brake pushrod clevis (Item 1) to the slack adjuster.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed from the vehicle, fasten the double diaphragm Anchorlok assembly to the mounting
                bracket. Tighten the two mounting nuts (Item 3) to 105 - 125 ft-lbs. (142 - 169 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install air lines to the spring brake and service brake chambers. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s04019_6.xml" xrefid="f0401909">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Uncage compression spring and reassemble release tool in side pocket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace dust plug in release tool keyhole in center of chamber.</para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>After reassembly, check for proper spring brake and service brake operation. Check brake
                        adjustment. Refer to GROUP 04 - AIR BRAKES in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
